intro: Eunanus cusickii, commonly known as the Cusick's milkvetch, is a flowering plant native to the arid regions of the southwestern United States and northwestern Mexico. It belongs to the legume family, Fabaceae, and is characterized by its compound leaves and small, pea-like flowers. The plant is adapted to survive in harsh, dry environments, often growing in sandy or rocky soils. Its seed pods, which contain several elliptical seeds, are an important food source for local wildlife. Eunanus cusickii plays a role in stabilizing soil and supporting biodiversity in its native habitat.
